visual_elements.description: Diagram A: Flag lot with labeled areas including Rear yard, Front yard, Interior side yard, and Street. Shows front lot line closest and most parallel to street. Front setback is 10' instead of 20'. Buildable area shaded.
Diagram B: Corner lot with Rear yard, Front yard, Interior side yard, and Street side yard labeled. Shows 16' setback on street side.

Diagram C: Substandard corner lot with frontage less than 50'. Rear yard, Front yard, Interior side yard, and Street side yard labeled. Street side setback is 10' instead of 16'. Front lot line is shortest of two frontages.
Diagram D: Through lot with Rear yard, Front yard, Interior side yard, and Street labeled. Buildable area shaded.
Diagram E: Wedge shaped lot with curved front yard and no rear lot lines. Rear yard determined by a 20' radius from intersection of side lot lines. Rear yard, Front yard, Interior side yard labeled.
Diagram F: Lot with more than 4 sides. Rear yard, Front yard, Interior side yard labeled. Rear lot line is farthest and most parallel to street.
Diagram G: Lot with more than 4 sides in an L-shape. Rear yard, Front yard, Interior side yard labeled.
